=24.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Slow vs Mitigation</span><hr size=1> Just had a thought when I was looking through the spell lists and AA abilities.  It seems that there is an emphasis (a small one albeit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) on damage mitigation for BL's with the Disciplines and the AA ablilities.  I'm wondering since this is a theme if maybe trading our slow spells for spells that reduce the amount of damage a mob does per blow would be a good idea?  My thought behind this is it would be useful to have a unique ability like this for raids and it doesn't seem too far fetched from the theme of the class.  (Plus it doesn't overbalance soloing since a 30% reduction per blow would come out the same as 30% fewer swings in the long run.)<br>
<br>
Gagalot<br>
Lvl 15 Noob Ogre<br>
<br>
ps - I have no clue how hard this would be to code in, but it seems like some of the code would already exist from the BL discipline. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/utipop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tipop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR color=#330066><CENTER>Beast Overlord</CENTER><HR color=#330066></span><br>  Posts: 718<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/9/02 11:51:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/minimark.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slow vs Mitigation</span><hr size=1> Interesting idea.  You should submit it.<br>
<br>
The counter-arguement is that reducing the damage a mob inflicts would then STACK with the slows from an enchanter or shaman, and possibly trivialize some encounters. <p><BR>
